snippet.textDisplay:
The song is good, my concern though is about the Music Video. Does this format mean that there would be a music video for every song? If you think that will still give us good songs, think again. Some of the best songs in previous seasons were so abstract that it would have been impossible to make music videos out of them. Brilliant songs like Kattey, Zariya, Yatra and Sati incorporated vastly different elements in them, which can’t be put in any video format. So my concern is, we are going to lose such abstract yet beautiful songs just because they would be rejected on the basis of “Music video”. The whole point of coke studio in my opinion was stepping outside the boundaries of typical Bollywood songs/ private album songs with videos and do something different. I think that purpose is lost here.
I don’t want to take anything away from Mr. Trivedi and the 2 fantastic singers, Jyoti Nooran and Harshdeep Kaur though. I enjoyed watching them perform.

snippet.textDisplay: Really disappointed with this season's format. I was looking forward for this since the time the promo came out. And the first thing I notice is only 1 song per artist, which was the first letdown. Next was the music video part. Why not scrap it and use the spare time for another song? There is no use of making it heard to the larger audience with the music video. It is just an insane way to promote it. Frankly the song is not bad, and the Honey SIngh fans that do not wish to listen to this are perfectly welcome not to. Don't force it on them by commercializing it in this way. Coke Studio Pakistan Season 7 was this utterly noisy and irritating season best left unheard, yet maybe I feel I would rather listen to that than this, just because its format was a little better. MTV, please take note.
